title.narrative: 01-04 IMMUNISATION

description.narrative: 1.4. By 2021, all districts in Zambia have their capacity increased to plan, resource and implement immunization programme for increased coverage of DPT3 vaccination with focus on the hardest to reach and marginalized communities., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2021, children (including newborns and adolescents) and pregnant women benefit from improved and equitable high-impact maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health interventions and behaviors.
